KANO – Abdulkarim Abdulsalam Zaura, a frontline Senatorial aspirant for Kano central under the platform of All Progressives Congress (APC) on Wednesday refuted speculations that he has been disqualified from the race. Contrary to the speculation that rocked Kano political firmament during the weekend, the top Bola Ahmed Tinubu ally has been cleared by the ruling APC to run. DAILY INDEPENDENT learnt that vested groups had filed petitions before the APC screening committee challenging the eligibility of Zaura, sighting an alleged criminal trial against the aspirant. -Advertisement- Briefing Newsmen in Kano on Wednesday on the development, Hajiya Balaraba Ibrahim, Aide to the APC stalwart explained that the purported disqualification was the handiwork of opponents. Ibrahim said that “those playing politics with issues of concerns would be disappointed by the end of balloting by the weekend.” Ibrahim described her principal as “a successful international businessman who has contributed immensely to social-economic development of Kano in particular, and Nigeria in general”, as she vowed that the senatorial aspirant would not be distracted by noise. She expressed surprise at why opponents of her principal employed underhand tactics instead of facing the forthcoming primary election headlong. Ibrahim stressed that “For the purpose of clarity, the APC screening committee has successfully cleared AA Zaura as an aspirant for Kano central senatorial seat. He would be taking part in the primary this weekend. POLL She assured: “We are aware of the petition written against Zaura. Those petitioners challenging the eligibility of Zaura simply because he answered no to a portion of the question, on whether or not he has a criminal trial.”